# Demo site copy

Use these exact labels on GitHub Pages demo detail pages and in `_data/demos.yml` comments.

## Primary GitHub CTA

- **Label:** `View on GitHub`
- **Target:** `github_doc` in `_data/demos.yml` (must be a file that exists in the repo)
- Do not use "View README on GitHub", "View source", or "View on GitHub repo"

## Secondary CTAs (active demos only)

| Label | When to show |
|---|---|
| `Setup guide` | Only when `setup_guide` differs from `github_doc` |
| `Import workflow JSON` | Active demos with `workflow_json` set |

## Link fields in demos.yml

| Field | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `github_doc` | Primary doc linked by "View on GitHub" — verify the file exists |
| `setup_guide` | Optional setup doc; omit or duplicate `github_doc` if setup IS the README |
| `workflow_json` | AO import JSON for active demos |
| `github_path` | Repo folder path for display only (e.g. planned artifacts note) |

Before adding or changing demo links, confirm the target file exists in git.
